## RPG (Role-Playing Game)

**What it is:** Character has stats, levels, gear, abilities. Players progress through quests, dungeons, PvP, or open-world adventure. Often anime-themed.

**Audience:** Older skew (12–25). Heavily male. Anime RPGs are a sub-niche dominated by Asia-Pacific players.

**Session shape:** 45–120 min per session. Long. Deep. Hardcore. Players grind for weeks for a rare item.

**Monetization fit:** **Strong.** Cosmetic gear, exclusive characters, fast travel, expanded inventory, season passes. Higher price tolerance because players invest more time. Cosmetics can be priced at 500–2,000 Robux.

**Build difficulty:** **5/5.** **Hardest genre on this list.** Combat networking, animation blending, hitbox sync, balance, content (quests/dungeons/maps). Solo dev with AI can build a *small* RPG — not a top-chart RPG. RPGs win on content depth, which takes a team or 2+ years.

**Saturation:** **3/5.** Roblox itself flagged RPGs as **underrepresented relative to demand** (Incubator/Jumpstart 2026). The 18+ audience wants more. Quality bar is high but the lane is genuinely open.

**Realistic earnings ceiling for a solo dev:** $1,000–$10,000/month if you can ship something genuinely fresh. Long ramp-up.

**Examples:** *Blox Fruits*, *Deepwoken*, *Anime Adventures*, *Type Soul*

**Verdict:** **High ceiling, high risk for solo.** Only attempt if (a) you genuinely love the genre and will iterate for 6+ months, or (b) you scope micro — single map, single combat system, deep enough to be sticky. The Roblox Incubator program could fund this if you have a unique angle.

