## OBBY (Obstacle Course)

**What it is:** Jump-and-die platformer. Reach the end. Sometimes there are 1,000+ stages. *Tower of Hell* etc.

**Audience:** Young (6–12), casual, drop-in/drop-out.

**Session shape:** 10–25 minutes per session, often 1 session/day. Single-session genre.

**Monetization fit:** Limited. Stage skips, cosmetic trails, gear cosmetics, VIP. Avoid pay-to-win on the obstacles themselves.

**Build difficulty:** **1/5.** The easiest genre to ship V1. Build stages, ship.

**Saturation:** **5/5.** Saturated and revenue-capped because session times are short and Creator Rewards favor longer engagement.

**Realistic earnings ceiling for a solo dev:** $50–$500/month for most. Rare breakouts (themed obbies, viral mechanic) can hit $1–5K/month.

**Verdict:** **Don't build this for revenue.** Build it as a learning project. Or as a B-game while your A-game is in production.

