## SOCIAL / ROLEPLAY (RP) / HANGOUT

**What it is:** Open-world social space. No goal. Players hang out, dress up, roleplay, chat. *Brookhaven*, *Adopt Me!* (technically pet-RP hybrid), most "town" games.

**Audience:** Young to teen, leans female, group-play heavy.

**Session shape:** **30–60+ min per session, deeply repeat-friendly.** This is where the longest sessions on Roblox happen. Voice chat (Spatial Voice) supercharges retention here.

**Monetization fit:** **Cosmetics dominate.** Outfits, accessories, emotes, housing, custom chat effects. High volume of small purchases. Lower per-purchase value, much higher purchase frequency.

**Build difficulty:** **3/5 architecturally**, **5/5 to actually retain players**. The *systems* are simple (chat, animations, housing); the *content cadence and community management* are the hard part.

**Saturation:** **5/5.** Brookhaven owns the lane. Adopt Me! owns the pet-RP lane. Trying to clone these is suicide.

**Realistic earnings ceiling for a solo dev:** $500–$5,000/month if you find a fresh angle (specific theme: "Coffee Shop RP", "Mall RP", "Hospital RP" — all exist and have communities).

**Verdict:** Hard to break in cold, but a niche themed RP (specific aesthetic + specific community) can carve out 1–10k DAU sustainably. Voice chat is the unfair advantage in 2026.

