## IDLE / INCREMENTAL

**What it is:** Passive progression. Numbers go up while you're offline. *Grow a Garden* is the dominant example. Adjacent to simulator, but the offline-progression mechanic is the differentiator.

**Audience:** **Surprisingly broad — including adults.** "Cozy" players, low-stress fans, working adults who can't sustain attention but want to "check in."

**Session shape:** **5–15 min per session, 3–8 sessions/day.** This is the algorithm-perfect shape for 2026 Roblox. Short, frequent, return-driven.

**Monetization fit:** Excellent. Speed-up boosts, premium seeds/units, cosmetics, expanded plot/inventory, exclusive offline-progression rates.

**Build difficulty:** **2/5.** Server-side timer logic + DataStore = most of the work. Visual polish is the moat.

**Saturation:** **3/5.** *Grow a Garden* defined the modern lane. There's room for themed variants (not garden — different cozy world).

**Realistic earnings ceiling for a solo dev:** $1,000–$10,000/month. Massive viral upside if a theme catches a moment.

**Verdict:** **One of the strongest fits for a solo beginner with AI.** Tight loop, perfect for the 2026 algorithm, mobile-friendly, monetization is clean, build difficulty is moderate. **Strong recommendation candidate.**

